snippet: In a state that Donald J. Trump won, many do not believe he will end a benefit they rely on, posing a challenge for those seeking to scrap the program....
abstract: Interviews with many voters in South Florida are skeptical Pres-elect Donald Trump will repeal Affordable Care Act, despite his many vows to do so; Florida has seen independent marketplaces, set up under law, gain more customers than any other state even as Floridians helped deliver presidency to Trump; state's situation underscores difficulty of repealing law, as many people across country, including Trump supporters, have come to depend on it.

byline.contributor: Robert Pear contributed reporting from Washington.

lead_paragraph: In a state that Donald J. Trump won, many do not believe he will end a benefit they rely on, posing a challenge for those seeking to scrap the program.

headline.main: Many in Florida Count on Obama’s Health Law, Even Amid Talk of Its Demise
headline.print_headline: Where Trump Won, Many Want to Keep Health Care

keywords.name: subject
keywords.value: Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act (2010)
